Greetings, Billiards Club members! I hope you all had a great summer. Our first official meeting of the semester will be held on Sunday, September 4, at 3pm in the Blackburn Dorm House.

Please be aware that as guests using residence hall facilities, the residents of the building have first priority over the space and use of the pool tables. This has not been a problem in the past, as the Blackburn House rec room has three tables.

To our new members who have not attended a meeting before, we are a recreational club intended for anyone who enjoys playing or is interested in learning how to play pool. There are no fees to join, as we rely on the use of the university's pool equipment and that brought by members.

Also! I encourage everyone to stop by the OSU Student Involvement Fair this Sunday, the 28th. It's the best opportunity there is to find new student organizations. VP Sanjay Luckwitz and I will be manning the Billiards Club table in the "special interests" section.
